<span id="freeTextContainer16715943807561555027">I&apos;ve been looking for an edition of this book for so long. The edition were sold out so fast I was even more determined to get it. Now, that the hype has toned down a bit, I was able to happily get my copy. I&apos;m so glad it didn&apos;t disappoint.<br/><br/>This is a book that is targeting Muslims wit the aim to encourage the &quot;rational thinking&quot; while understanding Islam and why it is chosen to be the last and the perfect religion?? People might ask, why do Muslims need to be told these things, they should know t</span>
  <span id="freeText16715943807561555027" style="display:none">I've been looking for an edition of this book for so long. The edition were sold out so fast I was even more determined to get it. Now, that the hype has toned down a bit, I was able to happily get my copy. I'm so glad it didn't disappoint.<br /><br />This is a book that is targeting Muslims wit the aim to encourage the "rational thinking" while understanding Islam and why it is chosen to be the last and the perfect religion?? People might ask, why do Muslims need to be told these things, they should know them already. Well, we don't. Thus, the average Muslim cannot explain Islam justly or in a rational manner. It's mainly, because we're born Muslims or some other lame explanation.<br /><br />This book, coming from an author who claims that he's specialized in comparative religion from a younger age, which is a pretty big claim. However, what I found in this book was a knowledgeable persuasive and objective presentation of ideas. I'm very impressed.<br /><br />This has given me such solid basis for rational thinking while trying to explain my religion to others or trying to clarify the misunderstanding in the age of media and its deception.<br /><br />==========<br /><br />كتاب رائع وأعتقد أن فيه من رد الشبهات من الحجج والبراهين ما كان خير دليل على تمكن الكاتب من العلم الذي يقول أنه امتهنه لفترة طويلة. سعدتُ جداً بقراءة الكتاب كما أن استفادتي من المنهجية التي اتبعها الكاتب في التفكير والاقناع كانت مثيرة للاهتمام ومفيدة جداً<br /><br />أعجبت بأن الموقف الذي تعرض له كان دافعاً له لأن يبحث في دينه بدلاً من الانسياق وراء الكلمات المتلألأة بزينة الحرية والتفكير النقدي بينما هي خاوية جوفاء تتكسر عند أقل ضغط. <br /><br />أعجبتني أبواب كثيرة إلا أن بابي "أم محجن" و"زميلتي المسيحية" كانا من أفضل الأبواب لدي.<br /><br />جزاه الله خيراً على نشر هذا الكتاب وجعله في موازين حسناته، فنحن في أشد الحاجة إلى مثله</span>
  <a data-text-id="16715943807561555027" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
